Virginia Beats Denver 14-8 in NCAA Lacrosse Semifinal; Maryland Plays Duke

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-05-28T22:44:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-28/virginia-beats-denver-14-8-in-ncaa-lacrosse-semifinal-maryland-plays-duke.html
The  University of Virginia  defeated
the University of Denver 14-8 in the first semifinal of the
college menâ€™s lacrosse tournament.  Virginia will play the University of Maryland or Duke
University in the  National Collegiate Athletic Association  final
May 30 at M&T Bank Stadium in Baltimore. Maryland and Duke play
later today.  Virginia, which had led 9-2 at halftime, got three goals
apiece from Steele Stanwick, Chris Bocklet and Mark Cockerton.
Goalie Adam Ghitelman had 10 saves for the Cavaliers.  Jeremy Noble led the scoring for the Pioneers with three
goals, while Jamie Faus recorded eight saves.  Both schools defeated higher-seeded teams to advance to the
semifinals. Virginia beat No. 2 Cornell 13-9 and Denver defeated
No. 3 Johns Hopkins 14-9 in quarterfinal games in Hempstead,  New
York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
